## API and DB conventions (refer to infra packages)

- **TypeScript client API or server API:** Follow the conventions and rules in the **http lib** — see [_thunderstorm/http/.rules/how-to-use.mdc](_thunderstorm/http/.rules/how-to-use.mdc). Use their patterns for `ApiDef`, decorators, and request/response typing.
- **DB storable entity:** Follow the conventions and rules in the **db-api lib** — see [_thunderstorm/db-api/.rules/how-to-use.mdc](_thunderstorm/db-api/.rules/how-to-use.mdc). Use their patterns for CRUD, collections, and persistence.

## BAI (Build and Install)
- BAI overview (entities, flow): _thunderstorm/.rules/operational/bai-overview.mdc
- BAI is the only way to do anything in this repo unless explicitly specified; never use pnpm.
- BAI is a CLI tool; it is **not** run via pnpm. Invoke it independently. See **BAI CLI** for how to run it: [_thunderstorm/.rules/operational/bai-cli.mdc](_thunderstorm/.rules/operational/bai-cli.mdc).
- To build `bai -up=<packages-regexp>` (use -up to build specific packages, otherwise it builds the entire monorepo)
- To run tests `bai -t -tt=<pure|firebase|playwright> -up=<packages-regexp>` (use -up to test specific packages, otherwise it tests the entire monorepo packages)
- To clean install and setup the mono `bai init` (only in extreme case)
- If adding a new package, for fast usability read [_thunderstorm/.rules/operational/project-structure.mdc](_thunderstorm/.rules/operational/project-structure.mdc) and the [rules index](_thunderstorm/.cursor/rules/index.mdc).

